OL,4,Csickle cell disease looks at hospital
OL,5,Ccare
OL,7,FShe said "We try our best to do the
OL,8,Fbest patient-centred medicine, and the
OL,9,Fdiscussion with her was that we tried
OL,10,Fto avoid a transfusion if we could."
OL,12,FWhen asked if an earlier transfusion
OL,13,Fcould have saved her she said
OL,14,Fcatastrophic emboli are difficult to
OL,15,Fsurvive whether you have anaemia or
OL,16,Fnot.
OL,18,FA pen portrait was read out revealing
OL,19,FIrene was a devoted mother.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
